OL,3,CJeremy Kyle denies 'belittling' TV
OL,4,Cshow guest at inquest
OL,6,FThe court was shown a number of clips
OL,7,Ffrom the show, including Mr Kyle
OL,8,Ftelling Mr Dymond: "Be a man, grow a
OL,9,Fpair of balls and tell her the goddam
OL,10,Ftruth."
OL,12,FAnother featured the presenter asking
OL,13,F"Has anyone got a shovel?" as Mr
OL,14,FDymond attempted to explain why he had
OL,15,Fbeen messaging another woman.
OL,17,FWarning: This video contains material
OL,18,Fthat some viewers may find distressing
OL,20,FThe court was shown clips of the
OL,21,Funaired programme
